5 781 M
(RFC-050: Access Control and Audit Co-Design) s
5 759 M
(Status: Draft) s
5 748 M
(Date: January 2026) s
5 737 M
(Author: Derrell Piper <ddp@eludom.net>) s
5 715 M
(------------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 693 M
(Abstract) s
5 671 M
(This RFC establishes the principle that access control and auditing must be designed toge) s
5 660 M
(ther, not separately. Every access control decision point produces three outputs: a decis) s
5 649 M
(ion, an effect, and a record. Audit policy is per-realm, with lean defaults.) s
5 627 M
(------------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 605 M
(Motivation) s
5 583 M
(Security systems often treat auditing as an afterthought\342\\200\\224bolted on after access c) s
5 572 M
(ontrol is designed. This leads to:) s
5 550 M
(- Incomplete coverage: Some decisions are never logged) s
5 539 M
(- Inconsistent records: Different formats at different points) s
5 528 M
(- Performance surprises: Auditing added late without cost analysis) s
5 517 M
(- Policy gaps: No framework for what to log when) s
5 495 M
(The solution: co-design access control and auditing from the start.) s
5 473 M
(------------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 451 M
(Design Principle) s
5 429 M
(Access control and auditing are co-designed, not bolted on.) s
5 407 M
(Every access control point has three outputs:) s
5 385 M
(+-------------------------------------+) s
5 374 M
(|         Access Control Point        |) s
5 363 M
(+-------------------------------------+) s
5 352 M
(| Input:  principal, action, context  |) s
5 341 M
(+-------------------------------------+) s
5 330 M
(| Output: decision \(grant | refuse\)   |) s
5 319 M
(|         effect   \(what happens\)     |) s
5 308 M
(|         record   \(audit entry\)      |) s
5 297 M
(|                  \342\\206\\223                  |) s
5 286 M
(|         policy \342\\206\\222 lean: print        |) s
5 275 M
(|                  paranoid: append   |) s
5 264 M
(+-------------------------------------+) s
5 242 M
(The Three Outputs) s
5 220 M
(1. Decision: Grant or refuse the requested action) s
5 209 M
(2. Effect: The consequence of the decision \(action performed, or refusal message\)) s
5 198 M
(3. Record: An audit entry capturing what happened) s
5 176 M
(Auditable vs. Audited) s
5 154 M
(- Auditable: The mechanism exists to log the event) s
5 143 M
(- Audited: The event is actively being logged) s
5 121 M
(All access control decisions are auditable. Whether they are audited depends on realm pol) s
5 110 M
(icy.) s
5 88 M
(------------------------------------------------------------------------------) s
5 66 M
(Per-Realm Audit Policy) s
5 44 M
(Each realm configures its own audit policy. The default is lean.) s
5 22 M
(Policy Levels) s
